

    
       I found a sonnet i wrote in gr 6  Fire  The beautiful red-hot flames are dancing Bright orange feathers are licking the log Delicate sparks in the air are prancing Out of the chimney goes black and grey smog A steady crackling that makes you sleepy An animal that is of hot, bright red An ancient tool once used in a tipi Laughing and crackling as soon as it’s fed There, I lie next to the fire that’s hot I stare and stare at the welcoming blaze Turning over to warm whatever’s not Slightly, I peer through the cloudiest haze I look at the fire of intense heat Mother comes and envelops it with peat.  
    
    
